=> Difference between Arrays.asList(), List.of(), new ArrayList<>()
    -> Arrays.asList()  → Fixed Size (set allowed)
    -> List.of()        → Immutable (nothing allowed)
    -> ArrayList        → Fully Mutable (everything allowed)

    | Feature         | Arrays.asList()  | List.of()       | new ArrayList<>()    |
    | --------------- | ---------------  | --------------- | ---------------------|
    | Add             | ❌               | ❌               | ✅                 |
    | Remove          | ❌               | ❌               | ✅                 |
    | Update (`set`)  | ✅               | ❌               | ✅                 |
    | Allows null     | ✅               | ❌               | ✅                 |
    | Fixed Size      | ✅               | N/A (Immutable)  | ❌                  |
    | Mutable         | Partial           | ❌               | ✅                 |
    | Backed by Array | ✅               | ❌               | ❌                 |
